%N A074488 a(1)=1, then "jump over next cube": a(n) = 2*(a(n-1)+1)^3-a(n-1).
%C A074488 The rule "jump over next something" can be varied, see A075694, A075695.
%F A074488 a(1)=1, a(n) = 2*(a(n-1)+1)^3-a(n-1).
%e A074488 a(1)=1; next cube is (a(1)+1)^3=8; "jump over" it: 8+(8-1)=15; a(2)=15; next cube is (a(2)+1)^3=4096; "jump over" it: 4096+(4096-15)=8177.
%p A074488 a(1) := 1; a(n) := 2*(a(n-1)+1)^2-a(n-1);
